name: Rae Isla - Thank you, I'm sorry, I love you

attributes.trait_type: Thank you, I'm sorry, I love you

metadata.description:
I learned, the hard way, that almost all conflict can be resolved by saying three things:

Thank you.

I'm sorry.

I love you.

Now, I try to say them often as I possibly can.

Written in New York City. Recorded in Seattle.

lyrics.text:
Heartache, is it always so
That someone wants to run away
And someone can't let go
Oh babe, you're always on my mind
You're the one who comforts me
When I get so behind

Thank you for everything that you've done
And I'm sorry if I wasn't enough
I love you and I always will
I know that things got rough
And I'm the one who messed it up
But I love you and I always will

Somehow I hope it's not the end
And I can be strong for you again
I wanna be the woman that you saw
I hope you're laughing through the tears
A lot can happen in a year
I promise you I'm gonna work so hard

Thank you for everything that you've done
And I'm sorry if I wasn't enough
I love you and I always will
I know that things got rough
And I'm the one who messed it up
But I love you and I always will

Maybe we could've been different
If I could be someone I'm not
I tried and I tried, to give it all I've got
Now it's the first time in my life
That I've said love is not enough

Oh, thank you for everything that you've done
And I'm sorry if I wasn't enough
I love you and I always will
I know that things got rough
And I'm the one who messed it up
But I love you and I always will

I always will
I always will
I always will
